00:36:14,933 --> 00:36:16,367
Unbelievable.

728
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:20,433
And all of this is in addition
to what comes as standard.

729
00:36:20,467 --> 00:36:23,600
Functioning air conditioning,
electric windows,

730
00:36:23,633 --> 00:36:27,867
air bags,
electric door mirrors,
two sunshine roofs.

731
00:36:29,367 --> 00:36:32,967
And the value for money
doesn't stop there.

732
00:36:33,067 --> 00:36:35,800
The scrap value of
this car is about,
let's say 200 quid.

733
00:36:35,833 --> 00:36:40,500
So if I crash it,
I'll be 60 quid better off.

734
00:36:41,833 --> 00:36:44,467
I can make money
by having an accident.

735
00:36:51,067 --> 00:36:55,233
I'll be honest,
I was deeply cynical of
this whole enterprise.

736
00:36:55,267 --> 00:37:00,667
But I just stood up and said,
"No way, you can't
buy 4x4s for 250 quid."

737
00:37:01,267 --> 00:37:02,967
And yet, here it is.

738
00:37:03,767 --> 00:37:05,533
It's not perfect.

739
00:37:05,933 --> 00:37:08,800
Rear view mirror is not there.

740
00:37:08,833 --> 00:37:09,900
Head rests have gone.

741
00:37:09,933 --> 00:37:12,367
Other than that,
there's air conditioning,

742
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:16,333
very nice stereo,
six CD multi-changer,
cassette player.

743
00:37:16,367 --> 00:37:17,900
Nice touch of history.

744
00:37:17,933 --> 00:37:19,633
Loads of speakers.

745
00:37:20,600 --> 00:37:23,233
It's brilliant. I've got wood.

746
00:37:23,667 --> 00:37:25,367
There.

747
00:37:29,900 --> 00:37:32,867
I actually wrote
a review of this car
when it was new.

748
00:37:32,900 --> 00:37:36,700
And I remember
being very impressed
at how good it was off-road.

749
00:37:36,733 --> 00:37:40,133
This has
a proper transfer box,
high and low range,

750
00:37:40,167 --> 00:37:42,067
and differential locks.

751
00:37:42,067 --> 00:37:46,233
It's only 1.8 litres,
but it is quite spritely.

752
00:37:46,267 --> 00:37:47,667
And it's very light.

753
00:37:47,700 --> 00:37:50,567
It's almost 400 kilograms
lighter than the other two.

754
00:37:50,600 --> 00:37:54,067
Mind you,
it wasn't all good news.

755
00:37:54,100 --> 00:37:55,500
The previous
owner did warn me

756
00:37:55,533 --> 00:37:58,233
that one of the brake
discs was slightly warped.

757
00:37:59,433 --> 00:38:01,333
What he didn't
actually say was that it's...

758
00:38:01,367 --> 00:38:03,433
Well, it appears to be
bent at right angles.

759
00:38:03,467 --> 00:38:07,500
When you brake,
the juddering is appalling.

760
00:38:08,233 --> 00:38:10,633
It really doesn't... God...

761
00:38:14,333 --> 00:38:19,400
CLARKSON:  Soon, we arrived
at Top Gear's  top-secret
lifestyle test track.

762
00:38:19,433 --> 00:38:21,800
Which is just
off Ladyhole Lane,

763
00:38:21,833 --> 00:38:25,233
one mile to the west
of the village of Edlaston.

764
00:38:26,500 --> 00:38:28,567
At this
state-of-the-art facility,

765
00:38:28,600 --> 00:38:31,867
we headed first to the indoor
winter testing centre.

766
00:38:31,900 --> 00:38:36,067
Where we discovered
our cars weren't much good
on the, erm...

767
00:38:36,067 --> 00:38:37,333
Inclines.

768
00:38:37,367 --> 00:38:39,533
Up, up the hill!

769
00:38:39,567 --> 00:38:40,733
(SQUEAKING)

770
00:38:40,767 --> 00:38:43,067
I'm trying to put it
in four wheel drive.

771
00:38:44,533 --> 00:38:47,533
Oh, no!
Something's gone wrong.

772
00:38:47,567 --> 00:38:51,567
Come on, no!
Why are you going backwards?

773
00:38:51,600 --> 00:38:53,067
I can't...

774
00:38:53,067 --> 00:38:54,767
(GROANS)

775
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:56,733
MAY: Bollocks.

776
00:38:56,767 --> 00:38:58,467
I can't get it...

777
00:38:59,233 --> 00:39:02,133
(CLARKSON LAUGHS)

778
00:39:02,167 --> 00:39:05,267
CLARKSON:  We were then told
to report
to the oval test track

779
00:39:05,300 --> 00:39:07,633
where we received a challenge.

780
00:39:08,233 --> 00:39:10,367
It's a game of tag.

781
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:12,233
You each have
a different start point

782
00:39:12,267 --> 00:39:14,533
on the top-secret
oval test track.

783
00:39:14,567 --> 00:39:16,400
And you each begin at once.

784
00:39:16,433 --> 00:39:18,367
The object is not
to be overtaken.

785
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:20,133
If you are, you're out.

786
00:39:20,167 --> 00:39:23,800
And to make
the test more relevant,
you will each have a ballast.

787
00:39:24,567 --> 00:39:25,567
A ballast?

788
00:39:25,600 --> 00:39:27,200
That's what it says,
a ballast.

789
00:39:30,733 --> 00:39:33,067
-Right, this is
the "a ballast".
-Yeah.

790
00:39:33,100 --> 00:39:34,833
-And actually, it is relevant.
-Is it?

791
00:39:34,867 --> 00:39:39,533
No, it is.
Because one of the leisure
activities done by SUV people

792
00:39:39,567 --> 00:39:42,300
is going on
holiday in a muddy field.

793
00:39:42,333 --> 00:39:46,100
Yes, yes.
What isn't relevant is
the size of my caravan.

794
00:39:46,133 --> 00:39:47,900
What do you mean?

795
00:39:47,933 --> 00:39:49,333
Why have I been
given such an enormous...
Look at the size of it.

796
00:39:49,367 --> 00:39:52,600
No, no, the caravan isn't big.
Your car is small.

797
00:39:52,633 --> 00:39:54,500
-He's right.
-Makes it look big.

798
00:39:57,867 --> 00:39:59,800
CLARKSON:  Eventually,
we stopped bickering

799
00:39:59,833 --> 00:40:01,933
and took our start
positions on the track.

800
00:40:01,967 --> 00:40:05,533
Where it turned out,
there was
a surprise late entry.

801
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:09,333
I know exactly who it is.

802
00:40:09,367 --> 00:40:12,800
That, ladies and gentlemen,
is not the Stig.

803
00:40:12,833 --> 00:40:16,300
That is  Top Gear's
top-secret leisure Stig.

804
00:40:16,333 --> 00:40:18,333
Useless driver.

805
00:40:18,367 --> 00:40:21,300
We use him only
for testing caravans.

806
00:40:22,700 --> 00:40:26,300
MAN: (ON RADIO)
Three, two, one, go.

807
00:40:29,733 --> 00:40:31,400
MAY:  Here we go.

808
00:40:31,433 --> 00:40:34,400
Testing, testing has begun.

809
00:40:34,433 --> 00:40:41,067
I'm now unleashing
the 134 horsepower
Vauxhall Vectra engine.

810
00:40:41,100 --> 00:40:44,467
Sadly though, leisure Stig's
driving was so slow,

811
00:40:44,500 --> 00:40:47,400
that soon he was causing
a bit of a traffic jam.

812
00:40:48,033 --> 00:40:49,400
Oh!

813
00:40:49,433 --> 00:40:51,400
MAY: Why have they given me
such a massive caravan?

814
00:40:51,433 --> 00:40:53,033
This is hopeless.

815
00:40:53,067 --> 00:40:54,767
CLARKSON:
Well, it could be worse.

816
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:58,700
I can feel the downforce
from my "a ballast",
and it's good.

817
00:40:59,133 --> 00:41:00,800
Argh!

818
00:41:00,833 --> 00:41:04,367
I've gone wrong.
It's hopeless.
I've crashed into myself.

819
00:41:05,633 --> 00:41:08,733
I mustn't be
overtaken or I'm out.

820
00:41:08,767 --> 00:41:12,800
Using the power of
the mighty Frontera,
I caught up with Hammond

821
00:41:12,833 --> 00:41:15,333
and tried to take
him on the inside,

822
00:41:15,367 --> 00:41:20,233
which meant going
onto the surface
designed to test suspension.

823
00:41:21,500 --> 00:41:24,267
This bit's even worse!

824
00:41:28,133 --> 00:41:32,800
Total chaos, and I've lost
all the ground
I made up there.

825
00:41:34,500 --> 00:41:36,900
Because leisure Stig
was so slow,

826
00:41:36,933 --> 00:41:39,800
even James was
getting impatient.

827
00:41:39,833 --> 00:41:41,500
Juddering, buffeting.

828
00:41:42,100 --> 00:41:43,133
Come on, Pinin.

829
00:41:43,167 --> 00:41:44,867
CLARKSON:  And violent.

830
00:41:48,767 --> 00:41:50,667
Oh, yes.

831
00:41:50,700 --> 00:41:53,567
He's losing the wheel.
Massive error by the Stig.

832
00:41:54,333 --> 00:41:56,067
Smoke is pouring off.

833
00:41:57,767 --> 00:42:00,333
Right, this time, Hammond,
you're going down!

834
00:42:01,867 --> 00:42:03,567
Ugh!

835
00:42:05,967 --> 00:42:07,667
Oh, no!

836
00:42:11,167 --> 00:42:13,200
(CLARKSON LAUGHS)

837
00:42:14,233 --> 00:42:16,400
Then Hammond made an error.

838
00:42:16,433 --> 00:42:18,133
HAMMOND:
I'm on the rough stuff.

839
00:42:18,900 --> 00:42:20,733
Oh, this is impossibly...

840
00:42:22,167 --> 00:42:24,100
CLARKSON: Oh, yeah.
I'm sorry, Hammond.

841
00:42:24,133 --> 00:42:26,267
We have overtaken you.
You are out.

842
00:42:29,633 --> 00:42:31,667
I think I've lost a wheel now.

843
00:42:31,700 --> 00:42:35,967
Lot of sparks.
It's barely controllable,
if I'm honest.

844
00:42:36,067 --> 00:42:37,700
(CLARKSON LAUGHING)

845
00:42:46,133 --> 00:42:48,900
Oh, now I can see
the problem here.

846
00:42:48,933 --> 00:42:52,367
CLARKSON:  Meanwhile,
my race was going well.

847
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:54,400
Yes, I've just done James May.

848
00:42:54,433 --> 00:42:56,200
He's somehow ended
up on the infield.

849
00:42:58,067 --> 00:43:00,833
That was
a catastrophic mistake.

850
00:43:00,867 --> 00:43:04,833
CLARKSON:  But sadly,
I overcooked it trying to take
leisure Stig.

851
00:43:06,867 --> 00:43:08,567
(SCREAMS)

852
00:43:10,767 --> 00:43:12,200
(GROANS)

853
00:43:12,233 --> 00:43:13,933
Lost my brakes completely.

854
00:43:16,733 --> 00:43:18,600
CLARKSON:
With 20 laps completed,

855
00:43:18,633 --> 00:43:21,233
leisure Stig had given up.

856
00:43:21,267 --> 00:43:24,167
Hammond still thought
he was in the contest,

857
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:26,300
and I had a problem.

858
00:43:26,333 --> 00:43:29,800
Steam coming from
the front of the Frontera.

859
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:33,333
Things are not
good in the Vauxhall.

860
00:43:33,367 --> 00:43:35,467
MAY: Yes, here we go,
I can have him.

861
00:43:35,500 --> 00:43:37,433
-Come on!
-Uh-oh.

862
00:43:38,433 --> 00:43:40,767
It's tight,
it's tight at the back.

863
00:43:42,500 --> 00:43:45,200
Manoeuvre attempt
by Jeremy Clarkson.

864
00:43:45,233 --> 00:43:47,067
Argh!

865
00:43:47,067 --> 00:43:48,867
(SCREAMING)

866
00:43:52,700 --> 00:43:54,133
(MAY LAUGHS)

867
00:43:54,167 --> 00:43:57,600
-He's up the bank.
-(HORN HONKS)

868
00:43:57,633 --> 00:44:00,600
I think we might have
lost sight of the rules
of this race slightly.

869
00:44:02,067 --> 00:44:05,067
MAY:  The producers had come
to the same conclusion.

870
00:44:05,100 --> 00:44:09,333
So we were told to
abandon the oval test track.

871
00:44:09,367 --> 00:44:11,700
And report to the drag strip.

872
00:44:11,733 --> 00:44:15,667
Where we would see which car
could get from nought to 60

873
00:44:15,700 --> 00:44:20,500
and then back to nought again
in the shortest
possible distance.

874
00:44:21,133 --> 00:44:23,233
-It's a good test, this.
-Yeah.

875
00:44:23,267 --> 00:44:26,733
It is, 'cause it
measures acceleration
and braking all in one go.

876
00:44:26,767 --> 00:44:28,300
Absolutely.

877
00:44:28,333 --> 00:44:30,933
MAY:  Leisure Stig went first
to lay down a benchmark.

878
00:44:30,967 --> 00:44:35,567
And as he was mid-run,
Jeremy noticed something.

879
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:38,667
If you don't stop in time...
(CLEARS THROAT)

880
00:44:38,700 --> 00:44:40,533
Then your day
suddenly gets a lot worse.

881
00:44:40,567 --> 00:44:42,833
CLARKSON: Wetter.
HAMMOND: Colder.

882
00:44:42,867 --> 00:44:44,400
MAY:  Luckily for leisure Stig,

883
00:44:44,433 --> 00:44:47,833
the Kia Sportage stopped
well short of the pond.

884
00:44:47,867 --> 00:44:50,300
And once this
point had been marked,

885
00:44:50,333 --> 00:44:53,700
Hammond took his
position on the start line.

886
00:44:53,733 --> 00:44:56,267
I think he's had a bit
of a hair transplant.

887
00:44:56,300 --> 00:44:57,800
Just look at his fringe.

888
00:44:57,833 --> 00:45:00,633
Seriously, look at his fringe
when he gets out.

889
00:45:00,667 --> 00:45:02,400
You don't have your fringe
transplanted, do you?

890
00:45:02,433 --> 00:45:06,167
Just, well, remember Rooney,
when he had that
forestation job done?

891
00:45:06,200 --> 00:45:07,633
You have a look.

892
00:45:07,667 --> 00:45:09,900
Okay. There's no
putting this off. Here we go.

893
00:45:12,767 --> 00:45:14,633
Come on, everything
you've got, Jeepie,

894
00:45:14,667 --> 00:45:16,567
I need you to
get to 60, quick.

895
00:45:18,467 --> 00:45:20,233
Forty.

896
00:45:20,967 --> 00:45:23,733
Oh, my God. I'm coming up
to the Stig's braking point...

897
00:45:24,933 --> 00:45:26,067
Oh, my God.

898
00:45:26,100 --> 00:45:27,867
On the brakes,
that's all I've got.

899
00:45:28,233 --> 00:45:29,933
That's all I've got.

900
00:45:32,400 --> 00:45:34,633
I can't brake any
harder than that.

901
00:45:35,933 --> 00:45:37,633
(LAUGHS)

902
00:45:39,733 --> 00:45:42,467
Did a bit of
excrement come out?

903
00:45:42,500 --> 00:45:45,567
I had to use all of
the brakes, I mean...

904
00:45:45,600 --> 00:45:48,233
And you haven't
actually started braking

905
00:45:48,267 --> 00:45:49,933
before you got to
the Stig's stop sign?

906
00:45:49,967 --> 00:45:51,633
No.

907
00:45:51,667 --> 00:45:53,467
CLARKSON:  That was
a bit of a worry,

908
00:45:53,500 --> 00:45:57,467
as Hammond's
Jeep was much faster
than my wounded Vauxhall.

909
00:45:58,300 --> 00:45:59,667
Here we go!

910
00:45:59,700 --> 00:46:04,933
Yes! It's a flying
start from Luton's finest.

911
00:46:04,967 --> 00:46:06,733
Five thousand rpm.

912
00:46:07,067 --> 00:46:08,833
Five-and-a-half.

913
00:46:09,133 --> 00:46:10,433
Looking good.

914
00:46:10,467 --> 00:46:12,167
There's the Stig's marker.

915
00:46:12,833 --> 00:46:14,500
And there's 60.

916
00:46:19,067 --> 00:46:20,867
(HAMMOND LAUGHS)

917
00:46:21,200 --> 00:46:22,300
Wow!

918
00:46:22,333 --> 00:46:25,600
Holy mother of God,
that was close!

919
00:46:25,633 --> 00:46:27,367
Oh, no.

920
00:46:27,400 --> 00:46:29,967
Do not pretend
you've got clean pants,
because I know you haven't.

921
00:46:30,067 --> 00:46:34,067
Many poos shot out of my ani.

922
00:46:34,067 --> 00:46:36,933
CLARKSON:  I didn't enjoy
my near-death experience,

923
00:46:36,967 --> 00:46:41,233
but in truth,
James enjoyed it even less.

924
00:46:41,267 --> 00:46:44,467
My car is
faster than your car.

925
00:46:44,500 --> 00:46:46,300
And its brakes are not bad.

926
00:46:46,333 --> 00:46:47,767
(SNICKERING)

927
00:46:47,800 --> 00:46:50,867
And I very nearly went into
the muddy pool of effluent.

928
00:46:50,900 --> 00:46:52,433
Didn't you?

929
00:46:52,467 --> 00:46:55,767
-My car's very light.
-Yeah?

930
00:46:55,800 --> 00:46:58,833
MAY:  Still clutching
at straws, I began my run.

931
00:46:59,633 --> 00:47:01,400
Here we go.

932
00:47:02,300 --> 00:47:04,133
It is a test of acceleration.

933
00:47:04,167 --> 00:47:06,067
And braking, and he has
neither of those things.

934
00:47:06,067 --> 00:47:07,733
No, he doesn't.

935
00:47:09,067 --> 00:47:10,733
Come on.

936
00:47:14,300 --> 00:47:15,967
Still accelerating.

937
00:47:16,433 --> 00:47:18,200
Thirty.

938
00:47:18,233 --> 00:47:19,933
Thirty-five.

939
00:47:21,100 --> 00:47:22,800
Still accelerating.

940
00:47:24,300 --> 00:47:25,600
Forty-five.

941
00:47:25,633 --> 00:47:27,733
Well, he can't get to 60,
can he?

942
00:47:29,100 --> 00:47:30,867
Fifty.

943
00:47:30,900 --> 00:47:32,600
Fifty-two.

944
00:47:32,933 --> 00:47:34,700
Ugh!

945
00:47:35,067 --> 00:47:37,167
(HAMMOND LAUGHS)

946
00:47:37,200 --> 00:47:39,067
-MAY: Bollocks.
-(CLARKSON LAUGHS)

947
00:47:39,100 --> 00:47:40,633
-HAMMOND: Oh, it's sinking.
-You know what he was?

948
00:47:40,667 --> 00:47:42,833
-He was committed.
-Well, yes.

949
00:47:42,867 --> 00:47:45,167
He was determined to reach 60.

950
00:47:45,200 --> 00:47:46,900
He didn't, did he?

951
00:47:47,833 --> 00:47:49,700
God, it's chuffing freezing.

952
00:47:49,733 --> 00:47:51,133
You went a bit far.

953
00:47:51,167 --> 00:47:53,433
Can we just get a flag
to mark his position?

954
00:47:53,467 --> 00:47:55,933
Don't just stand there,
you idiots, it's filling up.

955
00:47:55,967 --> 00:47:58,233
CLARKSON: James,
I've looked at the situation.

956
00:47:58,267 --> 00:48:00,800
And there's nothing we can do.

957
00:48:00,833 --> 00:48:04,467
So with that,
back to the studio.

958
00:48:04,500 --> 00:48:07,900
HAMMOND:  Except, it wasn't
back to the studio.

959
00:48:07,933 --> 00:48:11,600
Because we were then told
to modify our SUVs

960
00:48:11,633 --> 00:48:13,567
to make them more lifestyle-y.

961
00:48:13,600 --> 00:48:17,267
And then report to a car park.

962
00:48:17,300 --> 00:48:23,200
A few days later,
with our work completed,
I was the first to arrive.

963
00:48:31,833 --> 00:48:34,533
I mean, hello. Here it is.

964
00:48:34,567 --> 00:48:36,300
What I've done is bring out

965
00:48:36,333 --> 00:48:40,967
the Jeep's innate,
outdoorsy American feel.

966
00:48:41,067 --> 00:48:42,633
Up there, roof tent,

967
00:48:42,667 --> 00:48:44,300
which is the best
thing in the whole world.

968
00:48:44,333 --> 00:48:46,333
Winch, dinghy, wind surfer,

969
